Well here you go  sure sure sure:Tesla Inc. Chief Executive Officer Elon Mu=
sk unloaded $5 billion of stock in the electric-car maker, shortly after re=
stoking a social media debate over the tax treatment of billionaires=E2=80=
=99 shareholdings.The world=E2=80=99s richest person so far has disposed of=
 more than 4.5 million shares this week, according to regulatory filings. T=
hose were his first sales in more than five years.Musk, who frequently stok=
es controversy on Twitter, created a firestorm over the weekend with a surv=
ey asking whether he should sell part of his Tesla stake. While he portraye=
d his proposal as having to do with debate over the ultra-wealthy avoiding =
taxes, the filings released Wednesday show some of the transactions were pr=
e-arranged in mid-September -- weeks before the poll. He also didn=E2=80=99=
t mention in the tweets that he has millions of stock options that must be =
exercised before next August, when they expire.There are two sets of sales.=
 On Monday, he exercised 2.15 million stock options that were granted in 20=
12, paying about $13.4 million to acquire 2.15 million shares; then he sold=
 934,091 of those shares for about $1.1 billion.=C2=A0The Form 4 disclosure=
s for the exercise and sales are here and here. Footnote 1 of each of Musk=
=E2=80=99s Form 4s says:=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe transactions reported on this fo=
rm 4 were automatically effected pursuant to a Rule 10b5-1 trading plan pre=
viously adopted on September 14, 2021 and established by the reporting pers=
on for the purpose of an orderly sale of shares related to the exercises of=
 options scheduled to expire in 2022.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Actually it says that i=
n all caps. I like my readers so I rendered it in sentence case for readabi=
lity, but now I=E2=80=99m going to say it again in all caps, for accuracy b=
ut also for emphasis: =E2=80=9CTHE TRANSACTIONS REPORTED ON THIS FORM 4 WER=
E AUTOMATICALLY EFFECTED PURSUANT TO A RULE 10B5-1 TRADING PLAN PREVIOUSLY =
ADOPTED ON SEPTEMBER 14, 2021 AND ESTABLISHED BY THE REPORTING PERSON FOR T=
HE PURPOSE OF AN ORDERLY SALE OF SHARES RELATED TO THE EXERCISES OF OPTIONS=
 SCHEDULED TO EXPIRE IN 2022.=E2=80=9DOn Tuesday and Wednesday, he sold a t=
otal of about 3.6 million of the 170.5 million shares that he already owned=
 (i.e.=C2=A0not=C2=A0shares subject to options), for proceeds of about $3.9=
 billion. There are a bunch of Form 4s for these sales (here, here, here, h=
ere, here, here, here, here).[1] They do not mention a prearranged 10b5-1 p=
lan; presumably he decided to sell them this week, and then did.Some backgr=
ound. First, in September,=C2=A0a few weeks after he put this Rule 10b5-1 p=
lan in place,  he said publicly at a conference that =E2=80=9Ca huge block =
of options will sell in Q4 =E2=80=94=C2=A0because I have to or they=E2=80=
=99ll expire.=E2=80=9D[2] He  has 22,862,050 options in the tranche set to =
expire next August; he exercised 2.15 million of them on Monday, leaving hi=
m with about 20.7 million options in that =E2=80=9Chuge block=E2=80=9D that=
 he plans to =E2=80=9Csell in Q4.=E2=80=9DSecond, this past Saturday,   Mus=
k tweeted a poll. =E2=80=9CMuch is made lately of unrealized gains being a =
means of tax avoidance,=E2=80=9D  he wrote,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cso I propose sell=
ing 10% of my Tesla stock. Do you support this?=E2=80=9D In a second tweet,=
 he said =E2=80=9CI will abide by the results of this poll, whichever way i=
t goes.=E2=80=9D The poll closed on Sunday, with 57.9% of the votes in favo=
r of Musk selling 10% of his stock.It is not clear what =E2=80=9C10% of my =
Tesla stock=E2=80=9D means. At the time of the poll, Musk owned about 170.5=
 million shares of Tesla stock. But he was also, for legal purposes, the =
=E2=80=9Cbeneficial owner=E2=80=9D of another 73.5 million shares underlyin=
g options; Tesla=E2=80=99s filings show him owning 244 million shares. So i=
f Musk were to sell 10% of his stock that would mean selling somewhere betw=
een 17 million and 24 million shares, give or take.Discussion questions!=09=
On Monday, Musk sold about 0.9 million shares to pay taxes on his options e=
xercise, pursuant to a plan he put in place in September. Sorry, I mean, PU=
RSUANT TO A PLAN HE PUT IN PLACE IN SEPTEMBER. Do those shares count toward=
 the 17 million-ish shares that he has to sell because of his Twitter poll?=
=C2=A0=09Also, as of Monday afternoon, Musk owned 1,220,481=C2=A0more=C2=A0=
Tesla shares than he did on Saturday when he tweeted the poll: He bought 2.=
15 million shares (for $13.4 million, by exercising options granted in 2012=
) and sold 934,091=C2=A0of them (for about $1.1 billion). If you are counti=
ng these shares for his poll, should=C2=A0they count=C2=A0against=C2=A0his =
obligation to sell stock? If on Sunday he had to sell 17 million shares to =
satisfy his poll obligations, now does he have to sell 18.2 million?=09On T=
uesday and Wednesday, he sold 3.6 million of the 17ish million shares that =
he has to sell because of the poll. There doesn=E2=80=99t seem to be any=C2=
=A0reason to sell those shares other than the poll. How many shares does he=
 have to go? Is the answer 13.5 million (17ish million minus the 3.6ish mil=
lion he sold for poll-related reasons) or 12.5 million (17ish million minus=
 everything he sold so far this week) or something else?=09He has exercised=
 only 2.15 million of the 22.9 million=C2=A0options that he previously said=
 he will exercise this quarter, and sold only 0.9 million of the 10 million=
 or so shares that he said he will sell to pay taxes on those exercises.[3]=
 So presumably another 9 million or so shares of sales are coming this quar=
ter =E2=80=94=C2=A0i.e. in the next eight weeks =E2=80=94 under his prearra=
nged 10b5-1 plan for options exercises. Will those shares count toward his =
remaining poll obligations? If so, most of his remaining sales will be for =
options exercises. If not =E2=80=94=C2=A0if the poll and the options plan a=
re separate =E2=80=94 then he=E2=80=99ll be selling 22+ million more shares=
 this quarter.=09I said =E2=80=9Cthis quarter,=E2=80=9D but how long does h=
e get to satisfy his poll obligations? Musk and Twitter both seem impatient=
, and I suppose he=E2=80=99s going to get this done fast, but I=E2=80=99m n=
ot sure he has any strict obligations.=09How does that 10b5-1 plan work, an=
yway? The point of a  Rule 10b5-1 plan =E2=80=94=C2=A0we have   discussed t=
hem a few   times around here =E2=80=94=C2=A0is that it automates the tradi=
ng decision: When you=C2=A0don=E2=80=99t have any material nonpublic inform=
ation, you agree on a plan that gives up discretion on the timing and price=
 of trading decisions; then, you can automatically trade under the plan eve=
n if you later get material nonpublic information. One possible way to do t=
hat would be to say =E2=80=9Cexercise 2 million shares of options, and sell=
 half the shares, each day starting on Nov. 8 and going until we=E2=80=99ve=
 exercised all the options.=E2=80=9D But that doesn=E2=80=99t seem to be wh=
at his plan says, because it seems like he exercised options and sold share=
