G goes public, but you have to hold them for a few months afterward. If the=
 stock drops after TMTG goes public, you might not be able to get out immed=
iately. This is all not risk-free.=C2=A0But that $7=C2=A0billion is a lot o=
f cushion. It=E2=80=99s not a crazy trade.If you are a professional investo=
r and someone offered you the opportunity to invest in Trump=E2=80=99s imag=
inary company at a $7=C2=A0billion valuation, =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6 ??? I don=E2=80=99t give investing advice aroun=
d here! But it seems to me that DWAC shares are trading at very high prices=
 due to retail enthusiasm and political factors, and that it would be very =
