tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> rules say that</a=
>=C2=A0=E2=80=9CForm 4 must be filed within two business days following the=
 transaction date,=E2=80=9D which is why Musk waited until Wednesday to dis=
close his Monday trades, but he helpfully disclosed his Tuesday and Wednesd=
ay trades that same evening.) The Form 4 will say =E2=80=9Cthese sales were=
 pursuant to a 10b5-1 plan,=E2=80=9D but it won=E2=80=99t describe the term=
s of the plan; in particular, it won=E2=80=99t say if=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</=
em>sales are coming. If you are buying stock while the CEO is selling, not =
knowing that she=E2=80=99s selling, you might feel a bit aggrieved. Meanwhi=
le Musk adopted a 10b5-1 plan in September,=C2=A0<em>described it at a conf=
erence in September</em>, and then, when he was about to start selling stoc=
k automatically in November,=C2=A0<em>told everyone on Twitter that he=E2=
=80=99d be selling=C2=A0a bunch=C2=A0of stock=C2=A0</em>in a highly salient=
 way. Isn=E2=80=99t that=C2=A0<em>much better disclosure=C2=A0</em>than you=
=E2=80=99d expect to get from a public-company CEO selling his stock? Didn=
=E2=80=99t he tell you what he=E2=80=99d do in advance, even though he didn=
=E2=80=99t have to, even though it lowered his selling price and cost him t=
ens of millions of dollars? Isn=E2=80=99t that information that you=E2=80=
=99d want as a shareholder, and that other CEOs wouldn=E2=80=99t give you? =
Sure he did it in a weird annoying winking=C2=A0way, but he=E2=80=99s Elon =
Musk, you just gotta accept that. If you get past the winking weirdness, is=
n=E2=80=99t this a model of disclosure that other CEOs should follow?</li><=
