<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Trump SPAC PIPE</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The rough basic facts are that Donald =
Trump has an imaginary company called Trump Media &amp; Technology Group (T=
MTG), he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25665904.=
269658/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAt=
MjEvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQtdHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1hLXNwYWM_Y21=
waWQ9QkJEMTExMTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3=
NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBe5161a56" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> signed a deal</a> with a special purpose ac=
quisition company called Digital World Acquisition Company (DWAC) to take h=
is imaginary company public at a valuation of about $875 million, and the S=
PAC=E2=80=99s current trading price gives the imaginary company a valuation=
 of about $7=C2=A0billion.[11]=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you=
 are a professional investor and someone offers you the opportunity to inve=
st in Trump=E2=80=99s imaginary company at an $875 million valuation, I thi=
nk you should do it? I don=E2=80=99t give investing advice around here, and=
 you could have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25=
665904.269658/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMS8xMC8yMi9idXNpbmVzcy9kZ=
WFsYm9vay9ib2F6LXdlaW5zdGVpbi10cnVtcC1zcGFjLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B7c047a8d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">some ESG-ish reasons to stay away</a>. But buying someth=
ing worth $7 billion for $875 million seems like a good trade.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To be clear, you could reasonably disagree. You could =
have some=C2=A0<em>financial=C2=A0</em>reasons to stay away: Sure TMTG is t=
rading at a $7=C2=A0billion valuation=C2=A0<em>now</em>, but it could go be=
low $875 million=C2=A0<em>later</em>. That=E2=80=99s entirely possible, giv=
en that it is an imaginary company.=C2=A0It has disclosed no financial info=
rmation, no business plans, no nothing; the market=E2=80=99s belief that it=
 is worth $7=C2=A0billion is based on political loyalty and memes and some =
vague bluster from Trump.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Let=E2=80=
=99s sharpen the hypothetical and say that you are being offered the chance=
 to invest in a PIPE, a private investment in public equity, in the TMTG/DW=
AC deal. You have to commit now; when the SPAC deal closes and TMTG goes pu=
blic, you will have to hand over your cash and get your=C2=A0shares. If thi=
ngs happen in the interim =E2=80=94=C2=A0if, for instance, TMTG=C2=A0puts o=
ut=C2=A0some public disclosure of its financial statements, operations, bus=
iness plans, any of that stuff that companies have to disclose before going=
 public, and that disclosure is bad =E2=80=94=C2=A0then the stock might dro=
p, but you don=E2=80=99t get to change your mind. Let's also assume that yo=
u have to agree to lock up your shares for a while after closing: You can=
=E2=80=99t dump them as soon as the deal closes and TMTG goes public, but y=
ou have to hold them for a few months afterward. If the stock drops after T=
MTG goes public, you might not be able to get out immediately. This is all =
not risk-free.=C2=A0But that $7=C2=A0billion is a lot of cushion. It=E2=80=
=99s not a crazy trade.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a profes=
sional investor and someone offered you the opportunity to invest in Trump=
=E2=80=99s imaginary company at a $7=C2=A0billion valuation, =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=A6 ??? I don=E2=80=99t give investi=
ng advice around here! But it seems to me that DWAC shares are trading at v=
ery high prices due to retail enthusiasm and political factors, and that it=
 would be very hard for a professional investor to underwrite a $7=C2=A0bil=
lion valuation for a company that is at this point, I really must emphasize=
, imaginary. What do its financial statements or projections or business pl=
ans look like? Who is building the technology for its social media platform=
? I will not belabor these questions because no one actually cares, but if =
you are a professional being asked to underwrite a $7=C2=A0billion valuatio=
n you should probably care?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again you=
 could reasonably disagree! You could say, you know, the Trump brand is so =
powerful that any media-ish company he starts=C2=A0will be worth $50 billio=
n, so getting in at $7=C2=A0billion is a bargain. That=E2=80=99s fine! I am=
 not going to argue with you. Still, investing at $7=C2=A0billion with a lo=
ckup is an aggressive choice. Especially since you can just buy the publicl=
y traded stock of DWAC at that valuation, without locking up your money.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose there is some number between $875 m=
illion and $7 billion where you could get=C2=A0some<em>=C2=A0</em>professio=
nal investors to sign up.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25665904.269658/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
vb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMDgvc3BhYy10aWVkLXRvLXRydW1wLX=
MtbWVkaWEtdmVudHVyZS1zZWVrcy13YWxsLXN0cmVldC1iYWNraW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTEyM=
V9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90=
ZXJtPTIxMTExMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb2b=
11b3a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">Anyway</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digi=
tal World Acquisition Corp. has begun scheduling meetings with prospective =
investors for a private investment in public equity, or PIPE, transaction t=
o support its merger with Trump Media &amp; Technology Group, according to =
people with knowledge of the matter. While the PIPE=E2=80=99s terms haven=
